broken bar, squared E (except at l. 3 where it is lunate), lunate Σ, cursive Ω. At ll. 2 and 4, Π and Τ are crossed by slanting bars, which could indicate an abbreviation. Small H and Ο above Τ and Π at l. 4, small curved signs at the upper right of T at l. 2, T and Ν at l. 4. Small curved signs below Υ and inside Ω and Α at l. 2, which could be now decoration marks, now abbreviation marks.</p><!--measurements from Korhonen-->\n                                <locus from=\"line1\" to=\"line4\">Lines 1-4</locus>\n                                <dimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    <height unit=\"mm\">33-37</height>\n                                </dimensions>\n                                <locus from=\"line1\" to=\"line2\">Interlineation line 1 to 2</locus>\n                                <dimensions type=\"interlinear\">\n                                    <height unit=\"mm\">not recorded</height>\n                                </dimensions>\n                            </handNote>\n                        </handDesc>\n                    </physDesc>\n                    <history>\n                        <origin>\n                            <origPlace>\n                                <placeName type=\"ancient\" ref=\"http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462270\">Catina</placeName>\t\t\n                                <placeName type=\"modern\" ref=\"http://sws.geonames.org/2525068\">Catania</placeName> \n                            \t<geo>37.49223, 15.07041</geo>\n\t\t</origPlace>\n                            <origDate datingMethod=\"#julian\" notBefore-custom=\"0501\" notAfter-custom=\"0900\" precision=\"low\">6th — 9 century CE</origDate>\n                        </origin>\n                        <provenance type=\"found\" subtype=\"discovered\" notAfter=\"1766-11-21\">Original discovery not recorded, but probably from Catania; Tardìa, Cod. Bibl. Comunale Palermo Qq C 17 a, f. 136r mentions the inscription as coming from Catania, communicated to him by Torremuzza 21 November 1766.</provenance>\n                        <provenance type=\"observed\">Observed by Libertini in Museo Biscari, later by Korhonen in Magazzino superiore, Collezione Biscari (formerly sala VII 288).</provenance>\n                        <provenance type=\"observed\" subtype=\"autopsied\">None</provenance>\n                        <acquisition/>\n                    </history>\n                </msDesc>\n            </sourceDesc>\n        </fileDesc>\n        <encodingDesc>\n             <p>Encoded following the latest EpiDoc guidelines</p>\n             <xi:include href=\"../alists/ISicily-taxonomies.xml\">\n                 <xi:fallback>\n                     <p>Taxonomies for ISicily controlled values</p>\n                 </xi:fallback>\n             </xi:include>\n\t  <xi:include href=\"../alists/charDecl.xml\">\n\t     <xi:fallback>\n\t       <p>ISicily glyphs authority list</p>\n\t     </xi:fallback>\n\t   </xi:include>\n         </encodingDesc>\n        <profileDesc>\n            <calendarDesc>\n                <calendar xml:id=\"julian\">\n                    <p>Julian Calendar</p>\n                </calendar>\n            </calendarDesc>\n            <langUsage>\n                <language ident=\"en\">English</language>\n                <language ident=\"it\">Italian</language>\n                <language ident=\"grc\">Ancient Greek</language>\n                <language ident=\"la\">Latin</language>\n                <language ident=\"he\">Hebrew</language>\n                <language ident=\"phn\">Phoenician</language>\n                <language ident=\"xpu\">Punic</language>\n                <language ident=\"osc\">Oscan</language>\n                <language ident=\"xly\">Elymian</language>\n                <language ident=\"scx\">Sikel</language>\n                <language ident=\"sxc\">Sikan</language>\n            </langUsage>\n            <textClass>\n                <keywords scheme=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins.html\">\n                    <term ana=\"#function.funerary\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/92.html\">funerary</term>\n                </keywords>\n            </textClass>\n        </profileDesc>\n        <revisionDesc status=\"draft\">\n            <listChange>\n                <change when=\"2016-12-03\" who=\"#JCu\">James Cummings autogenerated EpiDoc output from database</change>\n                <change when=\"2019-09-29\" who=\"#AA\">Alex Antoniou Epidoc editing</change>\n            \t   <change when=\"2020-10-05\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova normalised Unicode</change>\n            \t   <change when=\"2020-10-08\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova updated list of languages</change>\n            \t\t<change when=\"2020-11-26\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova restructured bibliography</change>\n\t    <change when=\"2020-12-18\" who=\"#system\">Updated Zenodo DOI</change>\n            \t<change when=\"2021-01-19\" who=\"#SS\">renumbered files, uris and references</change>\n                <change when=\"2022-12-22\" who=\"#martaf\">Marta Fogagnolo revised the text encoding, added dimensions, translations and commentary</change>\n\t</listChange>\n        </revisionDesc>\n    </teiHeader>\n    <facsimile>\n        <surface type=\"front\">\n            <graphic n=\"screen\" url=\"ISic003289_tiled.tif\" height=\"3680px\" width=\"5520px\">\n                <desc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana</desc>\n            </graphic>\n            <graphic n=\"print\" url=\"ISic003289.jpg\" height=\"3680px\" width=\"5520px\">\n                <desc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana</desc>\n            </graphic>\n         </surface>\n    </facsimile>\n    <text>\n        <body>\n            <div type=\"edition\" xml:space=\"preserve\" xml:lang=\"grc\" resp=\"#martaf #AA\">\n                <ab>\n                    <lb n=\"0\"/><gap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"line\"/>\n                    <lb n=\"1\"/><gap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/><orig>ΖΙΕΙΑΔ<unclear>OMA</unclear></orig><gap reason=\"illegible\" quantity=\"3\" unit=\"character\"/><gap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/>\n                    <lb n=\"2\"/><gap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/> <w><expan><abbr>ἐτ</abbr><ex cert=\"low\">ῶν</ex></expan></w> <num value=\"40\">μ</num> <w>υἱὸς</w> <persName type=\"attested\"><name><expan><abbr>Ἰσιδώρα</abbr><ex>ς</ex></expan></name></persName> <gap reason=\"illegible\" quantity=\"1\" unit=\"character\"/><gap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/>\n                    <lb n=\"3\"/><gap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/> <w><supplied reason=\"lost\">κατ</supplied><unclear>ε</unclear>τέθει</w> <w>δὲ</w> <w>καὶ</w> <persName><name><w part=\"I\">Ἰσιδω<supplied reason=\"lost\">ρ</supplied></w> <gap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/></name></persName>\n                    <lb n=\"4\"/><gap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/><unclear>Υ</unclear>Τ<hi rend=\"superscript\">Η</hi> <w><expan><abbr>τ</abbr><ex>ῶν</ex></expan></w> <placeName type=\"ethnic\"><expan><abbr>Καταν</abbr><ex>ῶν</ex></expan></placeName> Π<hi rend=\"superscript\">Ο</hi>ΖΗ<unclear>Λ</unclear><gap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/>\n                    <lb n=\"5\"/><gap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"line\"/>\n                </ab>\n            </div>\n            <div type=\"apparatus\" resp=\"#martaf\">\n                <listApp>\n                    <app><note>Text based on photograph</note></app>\n                    <app loc=\"line 1\"><note>Korhonen: [---]ZIEIAΔΣIIΛIII[---]</note></app>\n                    <app loc=\"line 2\"><note>Libertini: υἱὸς Ἰσιδώρ(ας); Korhonen ET(---) M υἱός, Ἰσιδώρα +[---]. The small curved sign at the upper right of Τ could be an abbreviation for ων (see l. 4): ἐτ(ῶν) and the small sign above the Μ could indicate the numeral</note></app>\n                    <app loc=\"line 3\"><note>Libertini: ἐτέθει δὲ καὶ Ἰσιδώρα; Korhonen: [κατ]<unclear>ε</unclear>τέθει (i.e. κατετέθη) δὲ καὶ Ἰσιδώ[ρ-]</note></app>\n                    <app loc=\"line 4\"><note>According to Korhonen the first letter could also be a Κ. The small curved sign above the T and the N could be an abbreviation for ων (τ(ῶν) Καταν(ῶν), i.e. τῶν Καταν(αίων), see also Korhonen)</note></app>\n                </listApp>\n            </div>\n            <div type=\"translation\" xml:lang=\"en\" resp=\"#martaf\">\n                <p>… at the age of 40. The son of Isidora … were lied down and Isidor- … of the inhabitants of Catania…</p>\n            </div>\n            <div type=\"translation\" xml:lang=\"it\" resp=\"#martaf\">\n                <p>… all’età di 40 anni. Il figlio di Isidora … sono stati sepolti e Isidor- … degli abitanti di Catania…</p>\n            </div>\n            <div type=\"commentary\" resp=\"#martaf\">\n                <p>The epitaph is very fragmentary and the several abbreviations make it difficult to read. Palaeography suggests a date to the first Byzantine era. The text must have been an epitaph as suggested by the verb <foreign xml:lang=\"grc\">[---κατ]ετέθει</foreign> (i.e. <foreign xml:lang=\"grc\">κατετέθη</foreign>) at l. 3, which is used to indicate the act of burial. At l. 2 and l. 3 the female name <foreign xml:lang=\"grc\">Ἰσιδώρα</foreign> can be read (but, as Korhonen points out, the second mention could also have been the masculine name <foreign xml:lang=\"grc\">Ἰσιδώρος</foreign>), while at l. 4 the reading <foreign xml:lang=\"grc\">τ(ῶν) Καταν(ῶν)</foreign> (i.e. <foreign xml:lang=\"grc\">τῶν Καταναίων</foreign>) is likely and connects this inscription the city of Catania.</p>\n            </div>\n            <div type=\"bibliography\">\n                <listBibl type=\"edition\">\n                    <bibl type=\"corpus\" n=\"IMusCatania\">\n                        <citedRange>191</citedRange>\n                        <ptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/2EUC82DH\"/>\n                    <ref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028</ref></bibl>\n                    <bibl>\n                        <author>Libertini</author>\n                        <date>1930</date>\n                        <citedRange>318 no.10</citedRange>\n                        <ptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/SKUU2R8X\"/>\n                    <ref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001871\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001871</ref></bibl>\n                </listBibl>\n\t   <listBibl type=\"discussion\"><bibl/></listBibl>\n            </div>\n        </body>\n    </text>\n</TEI>\n",
